# API Test Suite
# Unified HTTP requests for testing the API
# Use with REST Client plugin in VS Code or similar tools

# =============================================================================
# CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================

# Base URL - Change this to match your environment
# Local development: http://localhost:8080
# Docker: http://localhost:8080
# Network: http://192.168.1.10:8080
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

# =============================================================================
# HEALTH CHECK
# =============================================================================

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Content-Type: application/json

# =============================================================================
# USER ENDPOINTS
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# USER ENDPOINTS
# =============================================================================

### Create User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "name": "John Doe"
}

### Get User by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{user_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

### Get User by ID (example with UUID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000
Content-Type: application/json

### Update User
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{user_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.updated@example.com",
  "name": "John Updated"
}

### Delete User
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{user_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

### List Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

### List Users with Pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users?limit=5&offset=0
Content-Type: application/json

### Create Multiple Users for Testing
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "name": "Alice Smith"
}

###

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "name": "Bob Johnson"
}

###

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "charlie@example.com",
  "name": "Charlie Brown"
}

# =============================================================================
# USER VALIDATION TESTS
# =============================================================================

### Test Invalid Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "name": "Test User"
}

### Test Missing Email Field
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User"
}

### Test Missing Name Field
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Test Empty Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "",
  "name": "Test User"
}

### Test Empty Name
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "name": ""
}

# =============================================================================
# PERFORMANCE TESTS
# =============================================================================

### Performance Test User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "perf@example.com",
  "name": "Performance Test User"
}

# =============================================================================
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# To use this file with REST Client plugin:
# 1. Install the REST Client extension in VS Code
# 2. Make sure the server is running: docker compose up -d
# 3. Click "Send Request" above any request to execute it
# 4. Use Ctrl+Alt+R (or Cmd+Alt+R on Mac) to run all requests in the file
# 5. Use Ctrl+Alt+L (or Cmd+Alt+L on Mac) to run the request under the cursor

# Environment Variables:
# - Replace {{user_id}} with actual UUID from create user response
# - Change @baseUrl variable to match your environment

# Testing Workflow:
# 1. Start with Health Check to verify service is running
# 2. Create users to get IDs for subsequent tests
# 3. Test GET operations with the returned IDs
# 4. Test validation scenarios
# 5. Test UPDATE and DELETE operations
# 6. Run performance tests

# Common Test Scenarios:
# - Happy path: Create → Get → Update → Delete
# - Validation: Invalid data, missing fields, malformed JSON
# - Error handling: Non-existent resources, server errors
# - Performance: Load testing with multiple requests
